!! On a surface

If $$U$$ and $$V$$ are the standard coordinate vector fields on $$M$$ and $$f\colon M \to \R^3$$ is a parametrized surface, we can write the [[area form|Integrals on Riemannian domains]] as it is relevant to integration as
$$
\det(U,V) =
\sqrt{\|f_u\|^2\|f_v\|^2 - \lang f_u,f_v \rang^2} =
\|f_u \times f_v\|.
$$

